bored any ideas on what i can do i don't want bored com or any online games here's some ideas get involved in service volunteer at the library children's museum senior citizen's center ask your parents if you can refinish a piece of old furniture for your bedroom you can get an old dresser or chest at a garage sale and make it very beautiful write a booklet of short stories let your imagination go ask your mom to write down one task you can do to help her each day then do it like clean a drawer closet dust shelves fold laundry etc watch old movies they are sooo romantic plant a small garden grow some tomatoes or flowers organize a talent show for you and all your friends to show something they can do write your life story including many of your favorite memories you will love reading it when you are older ask your mom if you can paint a pretty mural on your bedroom wall tell her if it doesn't turn out to please her you will be willing to paint it over at the end of the summer have friends over to paint little sections of it cut cool pictures and images from magazines and catalogs and make collages on cardboard learn how to make a braided rug out of strips of old clothes and rags go to the library and check out some good books read them you may never have a chance to read like this again ever ask your mom if you can learn to make some simple recipes and have dinner ready for her each evening she will love that and it is pretty fun to cook good luck i wish i had the free time you do it is a rare opportunity make use of it The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Garfield Blankets (graphic novel) Little Britain Surrealist techniques The Fairly OddParents Kurt Cobain Drill bit Chatsworth House Animal Crossing Aladdin (1992 film) Wood carving My Life as a Teenage Robot Great Teacher Onizuka Milton H. Erickson Calvin and Hobbes Librarian 50 First Dates Kitchen Tomato Marilyn Monroe The Tracey Ullman Show shorts The Ashlee Simpson Show Humphrey Bogart The Adventures of Pete 